## Comprehensive shadcn/ui Codebase Exploration Report

I've thoroughly explored the shadcn/ui codebase and identified the key patterns, structures, and architectural practices. Here's everything you need to understand how to build compound components following shadcn/ui conventions:

### 1. PROJECT DIRECTORY STRUCTURE

```
shadcn-ui/
├── apps/
│   └── v4/                          # Main documentation/demo app
│       ├── app/                     # Next.js app directory
│       ├── components/              # Page-level components
│       ├── hooks/                   # Custom hooks (e.g., use-mobile, use-is-mounted)
│       ├── lib/                     # Utilities (includes utils.ts with cn())
│       ├── registry/                # Component registry
│       │   ├── new-york-v4/         # Primary component styles
│       │   │   ├── ui/              # 57+ UI components
│       │   │   ├── lib/             # Shared utilities
│       │   │   └── hooks/           # Component-specific hooks
│       │   └── bases/               # Base configurations
│       └── styles/                  # Theme variations
├── packages/
│   ├── shadcn/                      # CLI tool for adding components
│   └── tests/                       # Test files
├── templates/                       # Project templates
└── skills/                          # Claude Code skills
```

### 2. OVERALL DIRECTORY STRUCTURE OF PROJECT

**Root Level:**
```
/private/var/folders/vq/9q38rw0x2455zr_whqcrjbhr0000gn/T/planmode-bench-wt-run-1775473475295-32i4so/
├── apps/v4/                         (Main Next.js app with 57+ components)
├── packages/
│   ├── shadcn/                      (CLI for component installation)
│   └── tests/                       (Test suite)
